      "creation_date" : 1719241019,
      "post_id" : 40485512,
      "comment_id" : 138688277,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "<i>&quot;since &#39;setActive&#39; implies you activate it at all times&quot;</i> Well, you can&#39;t really go wrong here, since Java is statically typed and you&#39;ll quickly discover that the method requires an argument. <code>setActive()</code> and <code>unsetActive()</code> is quite annoying since more often than not you&#39;d pick one based on a condition, and being able to simply pass on that condition to the setter is better than introducing <code>if</code>-statements."
