      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@aioobe how would you determine the condition in the first place? You are basically moving the if-statement to earlier in the process, but it is still there :-). If you are using CQRS, you won&#39;t have the condition either because you will be dispatching the predetermined command (<code>ActivateMyThing</code> or <code>DisactivateMyThing</code>) which have their own handlers who know exactly what method needs to be called on the model. Basically, you user is the if-statement because he picks the <code>activate</code> or <code>disactivate</code> button, after that, you no longer need if-statements."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 102965,
        "reputation" : 422600,
        "user_id" : 276052,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 80,
